♪The sun rests on the sea♪

2
00:00:18,310 --> 00:00:23,350
♪The sky steals the night and day♪

3
00:00:25,420 --> 00:00:30,340
♪The waves tug at my heartstrings♪

4
00:00:32,570 --> 00:00:37,290
♪That's the petals' curtain call♪

5
00:00:39,810 --> 00:00:44,500
♪The wind is blowing on my face♪

6
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:52,040
♪I'm stroking the fragile film♪

7
00:00:53,660 --> 00:00:59,100
♪Memories spread under the streetlamps♪

8
00:01:00,780 --> 00:01:06,410
♪The stars linger in the Milky Way♪

9
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:14,950
♪I've sung every song♪

10
00:01:15,330 --> 00:01:22,080
♪You remember it all♪

11
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:28,400
♪I cried, you laughed♪

12
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:32,260
♪You said you would be with me♪

13
00:01:32,260 --> 00:01:35,180
=Six Sisters=

14
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 29=

15
00:01:39,300 --> 00:01:41,380
I'll take care of you in the future.

16
00:01:43,610 --> 00:01:45,010
Just hearing that from you

17
00:01:46,210 --> 00:01:47,740
makes me happy.

18
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:49,900
About your future wife,

19
00:01:52,980 --> 00:01:55,380
have you discussed all the conditions?

20
00:01:55,380 --> 00:01:56,740
The two families will meet tomorrow.

21
00:01:57,740 --> 00:01:58,580
Alright.

22
00:01:59,850 --> 00:02:01,540
After you get married,

23
00:02:02,190 --> 00:02:04,460
will you live with your parents?

24
00:02:05,540 --> 00:02:06,740
I definitely would like to.

25
00:02:07,020 --> 00:02:08,980
But my Mom worries about you
and grand grandma.

26
00:02:09,540 --> 00:02:11,380
She'll probably stay here for now.

27
00:02:11,580 --> 00:02:12,560
Let's see what she decides then.

28
00:02:14,980 --> 00:02:17,700
You know your Mom has had
a hard time these years.

29
00:02:18,890 --> 00:02:19,780
After marriage,

30
00:02:19,780 --> 00:02:21,660
remember to treat her well.

31
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:24,220
She's been through a lot to be respected.

32
00:02:25,420 --> 00:02:27,060
You need to make sure that

33
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:30,140
Li Wen takes good care of her,

34
00:02:30,380 --> 00:02:32,980
and let her live comfortably, got it?

35
00:02:34,140 --> 00:02:35,100
Of course.

36
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:44,380
Why are you worried?

37
00:02:48,820 --> 00:02:49,660
Tomorrow,

38
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:51,780
are you sure you don't need me there?

39
00:02:51,980 --> 00:02:53,340
They're sending a woman to handle it.

40
00:02:53,780 --> 00:02:55,540
We can't possibly send a man, right?

41
00:02:58,540 --> 00:03:00,660
Don't worry, it's nothing serious.

42
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:05,140
No matter what they say tomorrow,

43
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:07,140
just agree first.

44
00:03:07,820 --> 00:03:09,100
If it's reasonable, I agree.

45
00:03:09,140 --> 00:03:10,820
If it's unreasonable, I won't agree.

46
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:14,700
Why?

47
00:03:15,260 --> 00:03:17,820
Are you afraid our son can't find a wife?

48
00:03:19,260 --> 00:03:20,780
He's tall

49
00:03:20,780 --> 00:03:22,260
and handsome.

50
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:23,820
He's got a good job,

51
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:25,100
and a great family.

52
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:29,420
Our son is picky.

53
00:03:30,220 --> 00:03:32,420
It's not easy for him to like someone.

54
00:03:33,260 --> 00:03:35,940
Don't worry. I can imagine

55
00:03:35,940 --> 00:03:37,780
what conditions Li Wen's mom will ask for.

56
00:03:37,940 --> 00:03:40,540
It's nothing more than a house
and betrothal gifts,

57
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:41,840
maybe some appliances.

58
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:43,820
Let's just go with the market standard.

59
00:03:45,730 --> 00:03:47,520
If we give the house to Xiangdong,

60
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:50,380
we'll have to keep living

61
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:51,580
with Mom here.

62
00:03:53,980 --> 00:03:55,140
I'm talking with you.

63
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:56,560
In my opinion,

64
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:59,420
we should pay Mom some rent each month.

65
00:04:01,540 --> 00:04:03,260
We live in our own house,

66
00:04:03,980 --> 00:04:05,140
why should we pay rent?

67
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:07,340
Mom won't say it out loud,

68
00:04:07,820 --> 00:04:09,540
but we should show some appreciation.

69
00:04:09,820 --> 00:04:11,820
Why do you think so much?

70
00:04:12,380 --> 00:04:13,820
Thinking more is always good.

71
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:16,460
Mrs. Li, try this,

72
00:04:17,140 --> 00:04:18,780
braised soft-shelled turtle.

73
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:20,140
We don't cook this at home.

74
00:04:20,540 --> 00:04:21,380
Indeed.

75
00:04:22,460 --> 00:04:24,140
It's the signature dish here.

76
00:04:24,460 --> 00:04:25,300
Wen, help yourself.

77
00:04:25,540 --> 00:04:26,380
Okay.

78
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:27,980
Xiangdong's Mom,

79
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:29,780
we're all happy today.

80
00:04:30,140 --> 00:04:31,980
- I'll be honest.
- Go ahead.

81
00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:35,020
I'm fully satisfied with Xiangdong.

82
00:04:36,580 --> 00:04:38,100
Wen is a good girl, too.

83
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:40,700
When it comes to marriage,

84
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:41,900
we have to follow the rules.

85
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:42,900
Of course.

86
00:04:43,140 --> 00:04:44,580
Other conditions aren't important.

87
00:04:45,140 --> 00:04:46,140
You must have one thing:

88
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:47,740
A house.

89
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:48,740
We have a house.

90
00:04:48,780 --> 00:04:50,380
It's already prepared.

91
00:04:50,660 --> 00:04:51,900
In the Longhu Community,

92
00:04:51,980 --> 00:04:52,980
two bedrooms.

93
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,980
Isn't it a bit small?

94
00:04:56,780 --> 00:04:58,340
It's enough for two people.

95
00:04:58,380 --> 00:04:59,820
What if they have kids?

96
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,020
It'll still be more than enough.

97
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:04,380
What if the elders come to stay?

98
00:05:04,580 --> 00:05:05,580
Sleep on the floor?

99
00:05:06,340 --> 00:05:09,220
You need a three-bedroom apartment at least.

100
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,580
Don't worry, Mrs. Li.

101
00:05:19,140 --> 00:05:20,820
We'll discuss it when we return.

102
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:22,380
We'll find a solution.

103
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:24,780
It's not a problem at all.

104
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:26,220
The worst is

105
00:05:26,220 --> 00:05:27,780
I retire early,

106
00:05:28,340 --> 00:05:30,260
and apply for a larger house.

107
00:05:30,660 --> 00:05:32,900
The problem will be solved.

108
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:34,220
Are you crazy?

109
00:05:34,340 --> 00:05:35,660
Aren't you aiming for county level leader?

110
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:39,220
After all this effort, now you give up?

111
00:05:39,220 --> 00:05:40,260
You've finally made it this far.

112
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:41,700
It's just a better title.

113
00:05:41,700 --> 00:05:44,580
No. Retirement benefits are different, too.

114
00:05:44,580 --> 00:05:46,580
What else can we do?

115
00:05:50,380 --> 00:05:51,540
How about we buy a house?

116
00:05:53,140 --> 00:05:54,020
A three-bedroom one?

117
00:05:54,820 --> 00:05:56,020
How much would that cost?

118
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:57,660
Do we have enough money?

119
00:05:59,140 --> 00:06:00,340
Li Wen's family is

120
00:06:00,340 --> 00:06:02,540
insistent on this issue.

121
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:04,220
It's understandable.

122
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:05,780
They want their daughter's future

123
00:06:05,780 --> 00:06:06,900
to be better.

124
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:09,220
Isn't this the negotiation stage?

125
00:06:09,220 --> 00:06:10,380
Everyone wants to settle it in one go.

126
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:14,140
- Grandma.
- Jianguo.

127
00:06:14,140 --> 00:06:15,460
You haven't slept?

128
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:21,580
I heard what you said.

129
00:06:22,580 --> 00:06:23,700
I heard everything.

130
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:26,340
Your hearing is working again.

131
00:06:27,820 --> 00:06:28,980
If you have no other choice,

132
00:06:29,340 --> 00:06:32,100
give this house to Xiangdong
for his marriage.

133
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:34,220
How can that be?

134
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:35,540
If

135
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:37,580
this house is given to him,

136
00:06:37,780 --> 00:06:38,700
where will you live?

137
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:41,780
Can't your mom and I stay with you?

138
00:06:42,820 --> 00:06:44,780
This house doesn't belong to anyone,

139
00:06:44,780 --> 00:06:46,660
how could you give it to Xiangdong?

140
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:51,220
Your dad married you to Jianguo back then

141
00:06:51,340 --> 00:06:54,220
just to find a son-in-law for old age care.

142
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:56,340
He even changed his son's surname.

143
00:06:56,580 --> 00:06:57,700
Xiangdong's surname is He.

144
00:06:57,820 --> 00:07:00,220
He's our family's eldest grandson,

145
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,140
our own grandson.

146
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:02,220
This house is given to him.

147
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:03,820
No one will object.

148
00:07:05,140 --> 00:07:05,980
Mom,

149
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:07,780
whom are you giving the house to?

150
00:07:08,140 --> 00:07:09,020
No one.

151
00:07:09,020 --> 00:07:09,860
You're here.

152
00:07:10,220 --> 00:07:11,660
Let's have a meeting.

153
00:07:11,780 --> 00:07:12,820
I've decided.

154
00:07:12,820 --> 00:07:15,380
Give this house to Xiangdong for marriage.

155
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:18,780
I don't agree.

156
00:07:20,380 --> 00:07:22,460
This meeting is unnecessary.

157
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:24,460
Grandma just mentioned it casually.

158
00:07:24,690 --> 00:07:25,660
It was a whim.

159
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,260
Even if Xiangdong doesn't marry,

160
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:28,660
he shouldn't get this house.

161
00:07:28,820 --> 00:07:30,340
You should discuss it further.

162
00:07:30,470 --> 00:07:31,380
I'm leaving now.

163
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:40,380
Mom, don't listen to Grandma.

164
00:07:40,380 --> 00:07:41,900
She didn't mean it seriously.

165
00:07:43,020 --> 00:07:45,220
Dad left this house for you.

166
00:07:45,660 --> 00:07:46,500
In the future,

167
00:07:47,140 --> 00:07:48,700
we six siblings will divide it.

168
00:07:49,220 --> 00:07:50,820
It has nothing to do with Xiangdong,

169
00:07:51,460 --> 00:07:53,820
- right?
- What you said is correct.

170
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,220
Why talk about dividing the house?

171
00:07:55,220 --> 00:07:57,220
Your Grandma and I are still doing well.

172
00:07:57,260 --> 00:07:59,100
- Yes.
- It's really unlucky.

173
00:07:59,100 --> 00:08:00,140
No one said we would divide it.

174
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:03,860
Also,

175
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:05,300
in the future,

176
00:08:06,140 --> 00:08:07,220
when Xiangdong gets married,

177
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:08,260
and has children,

178
00:08:09,460 --> 00:08:11,460
they shouldn't take He as their surname.

179
00:08:12,020 --> 00:08:14,220
Jianguo is the son-in-law for elder care,

180
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:16,460
but Xiangdong isn't.

181
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:18,660
They should get their surname Zhang.

182
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:21,300
Mom,

183
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:24,100
you're thinking way too far ahead.

184
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:25,700
If I don't think far,

185
00:08:25,780 --> 00:08:27,020
who will think it for me?

186
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:39,300
Jiali!

187
00:08:39,580 --> 00:08:40,980
Why are you so excited?

188
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:41,820
Where's Mom?

189
00:08:42,820 --> 00:08:44,580
She's out at the stall, not back yet.

190
00:08:45,940 --> 00:08:47,340
Xiaoling is back.

191
00:08:50,980 --> 00:08:51,820
Xiaoling is back?

192
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:52,790
Where is she?

193
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:53,640
What are you doing, Jiali?

194
00:08:54,220 --> 00:08:55,060
Mom,

195
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:56,500
Xiaoling is back.

196
00:08:56,740 --> 00:08:57,940
Xiaoling is back?

197
00:08:58,940 --> 00:09:00,580
She's not with me right now.

198
00:09:00,580 --> 00:09:02,220
She's staying at
Guyuan International Hotel.

199
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:03,820
Staying at a hotel?

200
00:09:04,340 --> 00:09:05,620
Why didn't she come home?

201
00:09:05,980 --> 00:09:07,580
She said she'll join us for dinner.

202
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:09,180
Having dinner tonight?

203
00:09:09,980 --> 00:09:12,180
You go to ask Jiawen, Jiayi, and Jiahuan

204
00:09:12,180 --> 00:09:13,220
to come here, hurry up.

205
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:14,580
- Okay.
- Jiaxi, you

206
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:16,180
go get some deli meats.

207
00:09:16,180 --> 00:09:17,220
Is all this really necessary?

208
00:09:17,220 --> 00:09:18,820
Just go.

209
00:09:18,820 --> 00:09:20,580
Hurry up! Buy enough.

210
00:09:20,580 --> 00:09:21,420
Okay.

211
00:09:25,580 --> 00:09:28,460
Xiaoling finally paid off the debt
and can come home.

212
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:32,100
Mom, stop walking around.

213
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:33,580
You make me dizzy.

214
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:38,940
Go to the alley entrance,

215
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:41,420
and check why is she taking so long?

216
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:42,580
No need, Mom.

217
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:43,580
She can find her way home.

218
00:09:43,580 --> 00:09:45,700
Whether I go or not,
she'll come back at the same time.

219
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:49,740
It's called "absence makes her fonder".

220
00:09:51,180 --> 00:09:53,180
Let's disappear for a few years too.

221
00:09:53,180 --> 00:09:54,420
Let's go to the South.

222
00:09:54,580 --> 00:09:55,980
When we return, we'll be appreciated.

223
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:56,820
Don't be jealous.

224
00:09:57,340 --> 00:09:58,460
I'm really jealous.

225
00:09:58,460 --> 00:10:00,740
What are you jealous of?

226
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:01,700
It's good for her to be back,

227
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:02,540
right?

228
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:05,980
Mom, sit down and rest for a bit.

229
00:10:06,180 --> 00:10:07,440
Save your energy, okay?

230
00:10:09,220 --> 00:10:10,420
Grandma is up, too.

231
00:10:10,620 --> 00:10:11,460
Okay.

232
00:10:12,580 --> 00:10:14,180
Sit and rest, Mom.

233
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:16,020
What's wrong?

234
00:10:18,820 --> 00:10:20,220
Fan put the word out.

235
00:10:21,820 --> 00:10:22,700
What did he say?

236
00:10:23,820 --> 00:10:25,100
He'll marry nobody but you.

237
00:10:25,220 --> 00:10:26,060
Stop nonsense.

238
00:10:26,180 --> 00:10:27,580
Who will marry him?

239
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:29,580
He said it himself.

240
00:10:30,460 --> 00:10:32,580
It's a once-in-a-lifetime chance.

241
00:10:32,580 --> 00:10:34,100
He will never miss it.

242
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,180
He's unwavering.

243
00:10:37,460 --> 00:10:38,980
He knows so many words?

244
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:41,420
I'm just saying it.

245
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:48,220
The key is he works at the Power Plant,

246
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:50,180
with a stable job and secure income.

247
00:10:52,820 --> 00:10:55,460
How's Fang doing lately?

248
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:02,500
Go out and check.

249
00:11:02,740 --> 00:11:04,700
Okay. I'm going, Mom, don't worry.

250
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:07,580
Look, I'm jogging out right now.

251
00:11:07,940 --> 00:11:09,580
Don't worry, I'll check it out.

252
00:11:09,580 --> 00:11:10,500
I'll wait here.

253
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:15,120
Mom!

254
00:11:15,220 --> 00:11:16,340
She's back!

255
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:54,980
Mom, I'm back now.

256
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:56,340
Why are you crying?

257
00:11:57,580 --> 00:12:01,580
You rarely call us all years.

258
00:12:01,940 --> 00:12:04,340
I never know if you're doing okay.

259
00:12:05,060 --> 00:12:06,060
She did call us,

260
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:07,580
but only to borrow money.

261
00:12:08,820 --> 00:12:11,580
Mom, I'm doing just fine.

262
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:17,500
- You've lost weight.
- You're back.

263
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:18,340
Jiali.

264
00:12:18,620 --> 00:12:19,500
Don't stand here.

265
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:20,340
Hurry inside.

266
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:21,460
Grandma is inside.

267
00:12:22,060 --> 00:12:22,900
Wait a moment.

268
00:12:24,220 --> 00:12:25,340
Come on in.

269
00:12:26,660 --> 00:12:28,860
(Huang)

270
00:12:31,820 --> 00:12:32,980
Let me introduce you.

271
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:34,580
This is my boyfriend Huang.

272
00:12:35,580 --> 00:12:36,580
I'm new here.

273
00:12:36,580 --> 00:12:37,500
Nice to meet you!

274
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:43,340
Don't just stand there,

275
00:12:43,580 --> 00:12:45,180
come in. Huang, right?

276
00:12:45,180 --> 00:12:46,020
Please, come in.

277
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:46,940
Let's go.

278
00:12:46,980 --> 00:12:47,820
Please come in.

279
00:13:07,980 --> 00:13:08,980
Let me introduce you.

280
00:13:09,180 --> 00:13:10,020
This is my Grandma.

281
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:11,720
Hello.

282
00:13:12,590 --> 00:13:15,340
Shouldn't the elders offer red envelopes?

283
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:16,560
This is the tradition in his hometown.

284
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:17,300
